<DOC><DOCNO> AP890908-0168 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-08-89 1838EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i AM-Panama-Protest     09-08 0155</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Panama-Protest,0160</SECOND><HEAD>Panamian Soldiers Break Up Student Protest</HEAD><DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Riot troopers firing tear gas onFriday broke up a crowd of high school students protesting theclosing of two schools this week for anti-government activity,witnesses said.   Students trying to block streets near Remon Cantera School werestopped by about 40 soldiers. The school is Panama's largest, withabout 4,000 students.   No arrests or injuries were reported in the two-hourdemonstration.   Remon Cantera was evacuated and Education Minister Juan BoscoBernal will decide whether to suspend classes, a ministry spokesmansaid.   The ministry earlier this week closed the National Instituteafter firebombs were found there. Authorities said students plannedto throw them at police. It shut the American Institute afteranti-government demonstrations.   Ministry officials say the ministry will close any schools whereanti-government demonstrations occur.   Two schools closed last month, one in Panama City and one inColon, remain shut.</TEXT></DOC>